<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="595" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,260,968]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,487,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Description. Measurements.</emphasis>
Male body length 
<quantity box="[701,819,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.005" pageId="4" pageNumber="595" unit="mm" value="10.05">10.05 mm</quantity>
; head width 
<quantity box="[963,1067,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.61" pageId="4" pageNumber="595" unit="mm" value="2.61">2.61 mm</quantity>
; crown length×width: 0.88× 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.06" pageId="4" pageNumber="595" unit="mm" value="1.06">1.06 mm</quantity>
; eye width 
<quantity box="[343,451,296,320]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="595" unit="mm" value="0.89">0.89 mm</quantity>
; frontoclypeus length 
<quantity box="[718,826,296,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.18" pageId="4" pageNumber="595" unit="mm" value="2.18">2.18 mm</quantity>
; clypellus length 
<quantity box="[1040,1148,296,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.01" pageId="4" pageNumber="595" unit="mm" value="1.01">1.01 mm</quantity>
; pronotum length×width 1.05× 
<quantity box="[214,317,332,357]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.11" pageId="4" pageNumber="595" unit="mm" value="3.11">3.11 mm</quantity>
; mesonotum+scutellum length 
<quantity box="[668,771,332,357]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.63" pageId="4" pageNumber="595" unit="mm" value="1.63">1.63 mm</quantity>
. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,260,968]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">
Crown light brown with a pair of darker maculae mesad of posteromedial eye corners (
<figureCitation box="[1186,1256,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12. 1,3,5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1884,1907]" captionTargetBox="[230,1295,198,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[217,1339,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. 1,3,5. Brasura sinistra sp. nov. Holotype: 1. habitus, dorsal vieW; 3. face; 5. habitus, lateral vieW; 2, 4, 6. Brasura piscinura sp. nov. Holotype: 2. habitus, dorsal vieW; 4. face; 6. habitus, lateral vieW; 7, 9, 11. Limentinus declinatus sp. nov. Holotype: 7. habitus, dorsal vieW; 9. face; 11. habitus, lateral vieW; 8, 10, 12. Tialidia hama sp. nov. Holotype: 8. habitus, dorsal vieW;10. face; 12. habitus, lateral vieW.Scale bars = 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242054/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Pronotum and mesonotum piceous with light brown granules; scutellum brown (
<figureCitation box="[909,980,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12. 1,3,5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1884,1907]" captionTargetBox="[230,1295,198,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[217,1339,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. 1,3,5. Brasura sinistra sp. nov. Holotype: 1. habitus, dorsal vieW; 3. face; 5. habitus, lateral vieW; 2, 4, 6. Brasura piscinura sp. nov. Holotype: 2. habitus, dorsal vieW; 4. face; 6. habitus, lateral vieW; 7, 9, 11. Limentinus declinatus sp. nov. Holotype: 7. habitus, dorsal vieW; 9. face; 11. habitus, lateral vieW; 8, 10, 12. Tialidia hama sp. nov. Holotype: 8. habitus, dorsal vieW;10. face; 12. habitus, lateral vieW.Scale bars = 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242054/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Elytra fuscous with light brown spots along veins, surface densely covered with numerous tiny pale spots (
<figureCitation box="[953,1060,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12. 1,3,5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1884,1907]" captionTargetBox="[230,1295,198,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[217,1339,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. 1,3,5. Brasura sinistra sp. nov. Holotype: 1. habitus, dorsal vieW; 3. face; 5. habitus, lateral vieW; 2, 4, 6. Brasura piscinura sp. nov. Holotype: 2. habitus, dorsal vieW; 4. face; 6. habitus, lateral vieW; 7, 9, 11. Limentinus declinatus sp. nov. Holotype: 7. habitus, dorsal vieW; 9. face; 11. habitus, lateral vieW; 8, 10, 12. Tialidia hama sp. nov. Holotype: 8. habitus, dorsal vieW;10. face; 12. habitus, lateral vieW.Scale bars = 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242054/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Figs 2, 6</figureCitation>
). Ratio of crown, pronotum and mesonotum midline is about 1:1.19:1.85.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,260,968]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,380,511,536]" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer without processes, broad and swollen caudodorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1113,1201,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES22–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[194,1398,220,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[171,1415,193,1906]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES22–28. Brasura piscinura sp. nov. Holotype:22. Pygofer and segment X, ventral vieW;23.Pygofer and segment X, lateral vieW; 24. Aedeagus, styles and connective, ventral vieW; 25. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral vieW; 26. Style, lateral vieW; 27. Connective, caudal vieW; 28. Subgenital plate, ventral vieW.Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242058/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Segment X broad, lateral margins conveX (
<figureCitation box="[420,503,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES22–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[194,1398,220,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[171,1415,193,1906]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES22–28. Brasura piscinura sp. nov. Holotype:22. Pygofer and segment X, ventral vieW;23.Pygofer and segment X, lateral vieW; 24. Aedeagus, styles and connective, ventral vieW; 25. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral vieW; 26. Style, lateral vieW; 27. Connective, caudal vieW; 28. Subgenital plate, ventral vieW.Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242058/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus moderately narrow with few short spines subbasally; distal half of shaft eXpanded, with row of numerous setiform spines on each side, strongly constricted subapically with apical section recurved to left; apeX widened and concave distally with serrated margin; gonopore lateral at midlength of shaft (
<figureCitation box="[159,291,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURES22–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[194,1398,220,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[171,1415,193,1906]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES22–28. Brasura piscinura sp. nov. Holotype:22. Pygofer and segment X, ventral vieW;23.Pygofer and segment X, lateral vieW; 24. Aedeagus, styles and connective, ventral vieW; 25. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral vieW; 26. Style, lateral vieW; 27. Connective, caudal vieW; 28. Subgenital plate, ventral vieW.Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242058/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Figs 24–25</figureCitation>
). Dorsal connective stick-like (
<figureCitation box="[640,725,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURES22–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[194,1398,220,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[171,1415,193,1906]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES22–28. Brasura piscinura sp. nov. Holotype:22. Pygofer and segment X, ventral vieW;23.Pygofer and segment X, lateral vieW; 24. Aedeagus, styles and connective, ventral vieW; 25. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral vieW; 26. Style, lateral vieW; 27. Connective, caudal vieW; 28. Subgenital plate, ventral vieW.Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242058/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Style very short, attenuated distally with blunt apeX (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1424,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURES22–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[194,1398,220,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[171,1415,193,1906]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES22–28. Brasura piscinura sp. nov. Holotype:22. Pygofer and segment X, ventral vieW;23.Pygofer and segment X, lateral vieW; 24. Aedeagus, styles and connective, ventral vieW; 25. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral vieW; 26. Style, lateral vieW; 27. Connective, caudal vieW; 28. Subgenital plate, ventral vieW.Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242058/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Connective asymmetrical with triangular base, anterior arms long and curved, apeX recurved (
<figureCitation box="[1211,1296,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURES22–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[194,1398,220,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[171,1415,193,1906]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES22–28. Brasura piscinura sp. nov. Holotype:22. Pygofer and segment X, ventral vieW;23.Pygofer and segment X, lateral vieW; 24. Aedeagus, styles and connective, ventral vieW; 25. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral vieW; 26. Style, lateral vieW; 27. Connective, caudal vieW; 28. Subgenital plate, ventral vieW.Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242058/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate slender, outer margin slightly conveX, rounded apically with fine spines (
<figureCitation box="[1029,1114,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES22–28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1936,1959]" captionTargetBox="[194,1398,220,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[171,1415,193,1906]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES22–28. Brasura piscinura sp. nov. Holotype:22. Pygofer and segment X, ventral vieW;23.Pygofer and segment X, lateral vieW; 24. Aedeagus, styles and connective, ventral vieW; 25. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral vieW; 26. Style, lateral vieW; 27. Connective, caudal vieW; 28. Subgenital plate, ventral vieW.Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242058/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="595">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
